{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Add PDF Document Attachment Functionality to Documents Site and CMS\n\nImplement the ability for users to attach PDF documents in the documents site, with corresponding management capabilities in the CMS.\n\nRequirements:\n\nFrontend (Documents Site):\n- Add file upload interface that accepts PDF files\n- Validate file type to ensure only PDF documents are uploaded\n- Display upload progress indicator during file transfer\n- Show attached PDF documents with preview thumbnails or icons\n- Enable users to view/download attached PDFs\n- Handle file size limits with clear error messages\n- Support multiple PDF attachments per document if applicable\n\nBackend/CMS:\n- Create PDF upload endpoint with proper validation\n- Store PDF files securely (cloud storage or file system)\n- Add database fields to track PDF attachments (filename, path, size, upload date)\n- Implement CMS interface for admins to upload/manage PDFs\n- Add ability to delete or replace existing PDF attachments in CMS\n- Generate metadata for uploaded PDFs (file size, page count if possible)\n\nTechnical Considerations:\n- Set appropriate file size limit (e.g., 10MB max)\n- Implement virus scanning for uploaded files\n- Ensure proper MIME type validation (application/pdf)\n- Handle duplicate filenames gracefully\n- Optimize storage and delivery (CDN integration if applicable)\n- Add appropriate access controls and permissions\n- Ensure mobile-responsive upload interface\n\nEdge Cases:\n- Handle corrupted or invalid PDF files\n- Manage upload failures and provide retry mechanism\n- Address concurrent uploads by multiple users\n- Handle documents with no PDF attachments gracefully",
  "title": "Add PDF attachment upload and management",
